    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="200"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Files: Lot M–88: Box 96: Germany–Treaty
                    VII</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Australian Minister for External Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EH2"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Evatt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State acknowledges the personal message of Dr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EH2">Evatt</persName>
                    <note n="88" xml:id="d200fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> and is giving it careful consideration.
                    The Secretary regrets that Dr. <persName corresp="#p_EH2">Evatt</persName>
                    believes that there is danger that the latest United States proposals on voting
                    will merely reproduce the friction and misunderstanding of the Paris Conference.
                    The Secretary has grave doubt that it will be possible, as Dr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EH2">Evatt</persName> suggests, to induce the Soviet Union to
                    depart completely from the pattern of having the preliminary text of the treaty
                    prepared by the Council of Foreign Ministers and for that reason has endeavored
                    to secure for the other Allied <pb facs="0536" n="502" xml:id="pg_502"/> States
                    a more active participation in the preparation of the preliminary text. As Dr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_EH2">Evatt</persName> is undoubtedly aware, the United
                    States has given aggressive support to the desire of Australia and other Allied
                    States to participate in the actual drafting of the peace settlement and has
                    joined with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BE1">Bevin</persName> in this effort.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-24">April 24,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
